        "title": "fix(sessions): use account names for direct display",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Use configured channel account names as the display fallback for direct session rows when the current label is only an opaque direct peer id.\n- Preserve existing precedence for explicit `displayName`, session labels, group display names, and meaningful origin labels.\n- Include the account-name fallback in `sessions.list` search so users can find the readable account name.\n\nCloses #79183\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Direct Feishu-style session rows can show the configured channel account name instead of an opaque direct peer id when no stronger label exists, and `sessions.list` search can find that readable account name.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch (`codex/session-display-account-name-79183-20260618`) with repository dependencies available, exercising the gateway session-list and search paths through the repository gateway test harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts --reporter=verbose\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal capture from the local OpenClaw gateway session run showed the changed behavior:\n\n```text\n✓ |gateway-core| ../../src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts > gateway session utils > direct channel session rows fall back to configured account names\n✓ |gateway-core| ../../src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts > gateway session utils > direct channel account names preserve labels and meaningful origin labels\n✓ |gateway-core| ../../src/gateway/session-utils.search.test.ts > listSessionsFromStore search > filters direct sessions by configured account display fallback\n\nTest Files  8 passed (8)\nTests  524 passed (524)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 49.90s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The gateway tests verify a direct Feishu-style session can resolve/display `Quote Assistant` from `channels.<channel>.accounts.<account>.name`, explicit labels and meaningful origin labels still win, and search finds sessions by the configured account display fallback. `git diff --check` produced no output.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live Feishu/OpenClaw runtime was not started in this environment; the focused gateway session-list/search test path above exercises the affected runtime projection logic.\n",
